Source: partconf
Section: debian-installer
Priority: standard
Maintainer: Debian Install System Team <debian-boot@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Martin Sjogren <sjogren@debian.org>, Thorsten Sauter <tsauter@gmx.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 4.0.0), libdebconf1-dev, libparted1.6-dev | libparted-dev, po-debconf (>= 0.5.3)
Standards-Version: 3.5.9

Package: partconf
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, partitioned-harddrives
Provides: made-filesystems, made-swapspace, mounted-partitions
XB-Installer-Menu-Item: 45
Description: Configure and Mount Partitions
 User friendly debian-installer program for creating file systems,
 swap partitions and mounting them in /target

Package: partconf-find-partitions
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: debian-installer utility for finding partitions
 Helper program for finding partitions and detecting their size and
 existing file system.

Package: partconf-mkfstab
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, di-utils-mapdevfs
Description: debian-installer utility for creating fstab file
 Helper program for createing fstab files in the new installed debian
 system.

